originalText.text: Wish I would have listened to the reviews before reserving. I reserved a space for 2 nights via the app ParkWhiz. Once I arrived they said they have too many monthly customers to allow of any more overnight customers. I’m not quite sure they’re still available on the ParkWhiz app for reservations anymore if that’s the case. Waste of time. The attendant didn’t really care.

originalText.text: Horrible, don’t book here they won’t take you. I also saw the attendant drive the car in front of me  drive into the wall. Would not honor park whiz or spot hero. Date was 5/6/23 at  aprox 11:10 am. So if your car was wrecked, they did it.

originalText.text: Reserved a spot in this garage days in advance through an app (Best Parking / Park Whiz). Got to garage in my time window and was told it was full and they couldn’t take me. Couldn’t provide an address of another City Parking garage nearby and I had to pay more to get undiscounted parking nearby.

originalText.text: I prepaid but I never ended up actually finding the entrance to the garage after having circled the block in the pouring rain several times looking for it.  Clearly, it is not well marked! Fortunately I ended up getting a spot on the street so all was not lost, but I would skip this place if you can. More aggravation than its worth...

originalText.text: I know it’s a busy location, and the rate is cheaper than others. But that doesn’t make the reason to have a staff with such a bad attitude. The space of this lot is very tight. Skip it unless you are not tight on time and you are ok with a staff like that.
